events.event_description: U.S. production of Other Biofuels increased from 2,000 b/d in 2020 to 19,000 b/d in 2023, driven by growth in renewable diesel byproducts.
events.citation: U.S. production of Other Biofuels increased from just 2,000 b/d in 2020 to 19,000 b/d in 2023.

events.event_description: Phillips 66's Rodeo Renewed project is expected to begin producing 10,000 b/d of sustainable aviation fuel (SAF) in summer 2024.
events.citation: Developers expect Phillips 66's Rodeo Renewed project to produce up to about 10,000 b/d of SAF beginning this summer

events.event_description: Diamond Green Diesel's Port Arthur SAF project is expected to produce 15,000 b/d of SAF by the end of 2024.
events.citation: they expect Diamond Green Diesel's Port Arthur SAF project to produce about 15,000 b/d of SAF by the end of the year

events.event_description: The White House set an ambitious goal to meet 100% of U.S. aviation fuel demand with SAF by 2050.
events.citation: The White House also set a goal of meeting 100% of U.S. aviation fuel demand with SAF by 2050.

events.event_description: At the start of 2024, U.S. SAF production capacity was 2,000 b/d, with only two plants operating: World Energy's plant in Paramount, California, and Montana Renewables' plant in Great Falls, Montana.
events.citation: At the beginning of 2024, U.S. SAF production capacity was only around 2,000 b/d, with only two plants capable of producing SAF: World Energy's plant in Paramount, California, and Montana Renewables' plant in Great Falls, Montana.
